Hey Friend!

My name is Sam and on this site you can learn a bit about me and see what I'm currently working on.

About Me

Scroll or click through to learn a bit about me and my journey with technology, both failures and successes, over the years!

2020 (14 Years Old)

The year of quarantine was the year of me diving into 3d printing. Having stumbled upon a{" "} 3d printed boat on TikTok I HAD to learn more. On July 12th I built my Ender 3 Pro. Since then, I've created an entire shelf worth of prints.

2021-2023 (15-16)

I was tasked to spend 25 hours on a project for school and I thought it would be perfect to make a game. Over 500 hours of graphic designing and coding for the first time later: Turtleburg! My edutainment RPG about the water crisis.

2023 (17 Years Old)

After Turtleburg, I wanted to dive into other parts of CS. So, I signed up for Kode With Klossy for the summer. I didn't expect to like web development much but ended up coming out with three languages and{" "} "EdVisor" .

2023 (17 Years Old)

Having finished KWK, I was inspired to do web development on my own. I wanted to start simple, {" "} my own website . That in which you are scrolling through right now, Thank You!

2023 (17 Years Old)

I wanted to diversify my summer and did the{" "} {" "} Girls Who Code SIP {" "} for game development. Here I made{" "} Cheezy Conundrum{" "} {" "} and learned alot about p5.js and JavaScript for game development.

2023 (17 Years Old)

I was inspired by my female in STEM summer that I founded a Girls STEM club at my school. Here I take on the role of teaching coding for our projects. The first project having been the{" "} {" "} website{" "} {" "} itself.

To be Determined

This is only the beginning, I have a long way to go before I make a real name for myself in computer science. Next steps: Code/Art!

Skills

I love to make things both for the general web and for edutainment purposes. Here are the tools I use:

Turtleburg - Built using Godot Engine, GDScript, Python, and Aseprite.
